Constructor Detail

CRecordTable

public CRecordTable()
Creates a new instance of CRecordTable data structure. This constructor initializes the columnNames Vector used to store field information of a result set (database query). The rows Vector is initialized to hold each individual result, represented as an instance of CRecordTable.Record, an implementation of RecordIF. And finally, the columnAliases Vector is initialized to store the client-side user friendly label for the database field name.

public int indexOf(RecordIF record)
indexOf returns the row index of the specified record in this table. This method first performs a reference comparison of the argument to the records in the table. search

public RecordSetIF search(java.lang.String field,
                          java.lang.Object value)
search browses the CRecordTable content for all rows that contain a value determined by the "value" parameter for the particular column, determined by the "field" parameter. This is a linear search algorithm. A more efficient search would involve sorting the elements and then performing a binary search.
Overrides:
search in class RecordSetAdapter
Parameters:
field:Ljava.lang.String - the column used to perform the search on given a value.
value:Ljava.lang.Object - the value that the column for each row must contain to be found in the result set.
Returns:
a Ljjb.toolbox.sql.RecordSetIF object containing the records found in the search.
